  "exampleVerdict": "Best generation: Discovery 5, for build quality and the revised post-2019 Ingenium. Worst generation: Discovery 3/4 on the 2.7 TDV6, where oil pump failure can take the engine out with little warning. Most reliable engine across the range: The 4.4 SDV8 — high replacement cost, but a genuinely low failure rate. Highest risk: The 3.0 TDV6/SDV6's crankshaft bearing failure, which is largely unrepairable once it starts."
